    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><salute>Dear Sir</salute></opener>
                <p>Inclosed are the sheets respecting <placeName ref="pl0076">Edinburgh</placeName>.
                    Let me entreat you carefully to look them over, see what is omitted or may be
                    corrected. &amp; then return them let me entreat you to shew them to no one on
                    any account which will much oblige</p>
                <closer><salute>y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> obed<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>
                            Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi></salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant</persName></signed>
                <dateline>Sept<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> 17<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>
                    1775.</dateline></closer>

                <postscript>
                    <p>are not the colliers &amp;c set free by a late act? Pray give me a little
                            acc<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> of the marriage contracts. are they as
                            <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0057">Jonston</title></bibl>
                        says?</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p><stamp type="handstamp"><placeName ref="pl0703">NORTHOP</placeName></stamp></p>
                <p><hi rend="superscript">Free</hi><persName ref="pe0015">RMost<gap reason="illegible" unit="letters" quantity="2"/></persName></p>
                <p><stamp type="postmark">20<lb/>SE</stamp></p>
            </div>
        </body>
